  $escape$csharp_game — Integrating C++ in Unreal: UE Macro System and UPROPERTY/UFUNCTION$escape$,
  $escape$When using C++ in Unreal Engine with csharp_game, understanding the UE macro system is crucial. Macros like UPROPERTY and UFUNCTION help expose variables and functions to the Unreal Engine editor. For instance, UPROPERTY allows you to serialize and display properties in the editor, while UFUNCTION enables you to create callable functions from Blueprints. To integrate garbage collection, ensure that all dynamically allocated memory is properly managed using smart pointers or containers. Additionally, be mindful of the differences between managed and unmanaged memory to avoid common pitfalls.$escape$,
  $escape$public: 
UPROPERTY(EditAnywhere)
int32 exampleProperty;

UFUNCTION()
void exampleFunction() {
    // Code here
}$escape$,
  $escape$cpp$escape$,
