INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '2aa6e074-ea10-4a19-b220-1bb3f7b46441',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$csharp_game Modding Support — Exposing APIs to Lua$escape$,
  $escape$csharp_game developers can leverage Lua for sandboxed scripting and community extensibility. By exposing C# APIs to Lua, you can create a flexible modding framework. Start by creating a Lua state using the `LuaState` class from the `csharp_game.Lua` namespace. Then, use the `RegisterFunction` method to expose C# functions to Lua. For example, you can expose a `SpawnEntity` function to allow modders to spawn custom entities. To ensure security, use the `LuaSandbox` class to restrict Lua script access to sensitive game data.$escape$,
  $escape$using csharp_game.Lua; var luaState = new LuaState(); luaState.RegisterFunction("SpawnEntity", (entityName) => { /* spawn entity logic */ });$escape$,
  $escape$csharp$escape$,
